.IX Title "Net::Mollom::ContentCheck 3"
.TH Net::Mollom::ContentCheck 3 "2009-03-01" "perl v5.8.8" "User Contributed Perl Documentation"
.SH "NAME"
Net::Mollom::ContentCheck
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
The results of the \f(CW\*(C`mollom.checkContent\*(C'\fR XML-RPC call.
.PP
.Vb 5
\&    my $mollom = Net::Mollom->new(...);
\&    my $check = $mollom->check_content(
\&        post_title => $title,
\&        post_body  => $body,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
.Vb 5
\&    if( $check->is_spam ) {
\&        warn "someone's trying to sell us v1@grA!"
\&    } elsif( $check->quality < .5 ) {
\&        warn "someone might be trying to flame us!"
\&    }
.Ve
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
You should not construct an object of this class by yourself. Instead
it should be done by Net::Mollom's call to \f(CW\*(C`check_content()\*(C'\fR. After
you get one, these are the methods you can call.
.Sh "is_spam"
.IX Subsection "is_spam"
Returns true if the content sent was spam.
.Sh "is_ham"
.IX Subsection "is_ham"
Returns true if the content sent was not spam.
.Sh "is_unsure"
.IX Subsection "is_unsure"
Returns true if Mollom isn't completely sure if this comment was spam or ham.
.Sh "quality"
.IX Subsection "quality"
A real number between 0 and 1 that's shows the quality of the content
posted. 0 being the worst and 1 being the best.
.Sh "session_id"
.IX Subsection "session_id"
The \s-1ID\s0 of the Mollom session that this check was part of. This can be
saved and used later (ie, you need to call \f(CW\*(C`send_feedback\*(C'\fR for some
content after some time in the future).
